  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Cambridge Bible for Schools and Colleges",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "I rent my garment and my mantle",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] Ezra’s conduct betrays his surprise, his grief, and his indignation. The rending of the clothes is frequently mentioned in Scripture as a sign of grief: Ezra here is described as rending the under-garment or tunic (the ‘begedh’) and the long loose robe (the m‘îl) in which he was attired. Reuben rent his ‘clothes’ (plur. of ‘begedh’) on not finding Joseph (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Genesis 37:29",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "): Jacob rent his ‘garments’ (plur. of ‘simlah’) on seeing Joseph’s blood-stained coat (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Genesis 37:34",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "): Joseph’s brethren rent their clothers (plur. of ‘simlah’) when the cup was found in Benjamin’s sack (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Genesis 44:13",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "): Joshua rent his ‘clothes’ (plur. of ‘simlah’) after the repulse at Ai (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Joshua 7:6",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "): Jephthah rent his clothes (plur. of ‘begedh’) on meeting his daughter (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Jdg 11:35",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "): the messenger from the field of Ziklag came with his clothes (plur. of ‘begedh’) rent (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Samuel 1:2",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Samuel 4:12",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "): Job rent his mantle (‘m‘îl’) on hearing of his children’s death (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Job 1:20",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), and his friends rent each one his mantle (‘m‘îl’) when they came to visit him (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Job 2:12",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). These were all signs of grief. The action also denoted ‘horror’ on receiving intelligence or hearing words, which shocked: thus Hezekiah and his ministers rent their clothes (plur. of ‘begedh’) after Rabshakeh’s speech (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Kings 18:37",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Kings 19:1",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "): Mordecai rent his clothes (plur. of ‘begedh’) on hearing of Haman’s determination (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Esther 4:1",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "): the High-priest rent his garments on hearing the testimony of Jesus (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 26:65",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). See also ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Isaiah 36:22",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Jeremiah 41:5",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 34:27",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The ‘mantle’ was a long flowing robe; by this name is designated the High-priest’s robe (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 28:31",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 28:34",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 39:22-23",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "); the ‘robe’ which Hannah made for Samuel (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Samuel 2:19",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "); Jonathan’s ‘robe’, which he presented to David (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Samuel 18:4",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "); Samuel’s robe (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Samuel 15:27",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "); Saul’s ‘robe’ (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Samuel 24:4",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "); the ‘robe’ which covered the apparition of Samuel (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Samuel 28:14",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). Its use in metaphor (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 109:29",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Isaiah 59:17",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") agrees with this.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "and pluckt off the hair",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " &c.] This sign of grief is not described elsewhere in the O. T. Compare Esther (additions to), Esther 14:2, ‘All the places of her joy she filled with her torn hair’.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The shaven head was a common sign of mourning, e.g. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Job 1:20",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Ezekiel 7:18",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Amos 8:10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Ezra’s action denotes in an exaggerated way his great grief.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
